SIMPLE: sapajou
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sapajou
<hw>Sap"a*jou</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>sapajou</ets>, <ets>sajou</ets>, Braz. <ets>sajuassu</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of several species of South American
monkeys of the genus <gen>Cebus</gen>, having long and prehensile tails.
Some of the species are called also <stype>capuchins</stype>. The bonnet
sapajou (<spn>Cebus subcristatus</spn>), the golden-handed sapajou
(<spn>Cebus chrysopus</spn>), and the white-throated sapajou (<spn>Cebus
hypoleucus</spn>) are well known species. See
<er>Capuchin</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sapan wood</ent>⟦br⟧
